So we have `0 < k - m` and `k - m вүӨ n`.
From `0 < k - m`, we get `k - m вүҘ 1`.
From `k - m вүӨ n`, we can subtract 1 from both sides (valid since `n вүҘ 0`) to get `k - m - 1 < n`.

This is exactly the goal `k - m - 1 < vs.length` (since `vs.length = n`).

The following tactics will complete this proof:
```tactics
